OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1774469469
OL,3,CThe little plant that's helping save
OL,4,Cthe planet
OL,6,FPeatlands are our biggest store of
OL,7,Fcarbon. Whilst they only cover about
OL,8,F4% of the world's surface, they store
OL,9,Fa third of all soil carbon - twice as
OL,10,Fmuch as rainforests.
OL,12,FAs peatlands continually form peat
OL,13,Fthey are able to sequester (absorb)
OL,14,Feven more carbon from the atmosphere,
OL,15,Fmaking them a vital natural resource
OL,16,Fin our fight against the climate
OL,17,Femergency.
OL,19,FWhy do we need to restore peatlands?
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
