PN,39607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1774469469
OL,3,CThe little plant that's helping save
OL,4,Cthe planet
OL,6,FSphagnum moss is able to absorb up to
OL,7,F20 times its own weight in water
OL,8,Facting like a giant sponge, absorbing
OL,9,Frainfall and releasing it slowly.
OL,10,FPeatlands can therefore act as amazing
OL,11,Fnatural flood mitigators.
OL,13,FHowever, if a peatland is dry and
OL,14,Fdegraded then the water will run
OL,15,Fstraight off the surface straight into
OL,16,Fwater courses and can actually make
OL,17,Fflooding worse.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
